---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why Astro + Decap CMS"
  description="A modern content publishing workflow for business teams."
>
  <section class="astro-hero full-screen">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Astro + Decap CMS + Cloudflare</p>
      <h1>Modern websites where business teams own the content.</h1>
      <p>
        Astro gives IT a fast, secure, developer-controlled website foundation.
        Decap CMS gives business users a simple way to update text, images, and resources.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="image-placeholder large">
      Editable hero image placeholder
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split-section">
    <div class="image-placeholder">
      Content image placeholder
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2>Content can change without touching layout</h2>
      <p>
        Business teams can update page text, resource links, and image URLs through Decap CMS.
        Those changes are stored as Markdown content and published through GitHub.
      </p>
      <p>
        Layout changes, page structure, reusable components, and styling remain controlled in
        Astro files such as <code>.astro</code>, <code>.html</code>, and CSS.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-grid">
    <article>
      <div class="image-placeholder small">Image</div>
      <h3>Content-driven</h3>
      <p>Astro is designed for content-rich sites such as landing pages, blogs, documentation, and marketing sites.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <div class="image-placeholder small">Image</div>
      <h3>Fast by default</h3>
      <p>Astro reduces unnecessary client-side JavaScript, which helps public pages load quickly.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <div class="image-placeholder small">Image</div>
      <h3>Server-first</h3>
      <p>Pages can render on the server or be prebuilt, keeping the user experience fast and simple.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <div class="image-placeholder small">Image</div>
      <h3>Easy to maintain</h3>
      <p>Business content lives in Markdown. Developer-owned layout lives in Astro components.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="ownership-section">
    <h2>Clear ownership model</h2>

    <div class="ownership-grid">
      <div>
        <h3>Business-editable</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Page titles</li>
          <li>Body text</li>
          <li>Image URLs</li>
          <li>R2 resource links</li>
          <li>Download descriptions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Developer-owned</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Page layout</li>
          <li>Components</li>
          <li>Navigation</li>
          <li>Design system</li>
          <li>Security and deployment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>